Anglo American Platinum Workers to Vote on Strike as Pay Talks Break Down

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-07-07T13:14:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-07/anglo-american-platinum-workers-to-vote-on-strike-as-pay-talks-break-down.html
Anglo American Platinum Ltd. workers
represented by the  National Union of Mineworkers  in  South Africa 
will vote on whether to go on strike after pay talks held today
failed to secure an agreement.  “The NUM took a decision not to continue with talks with
the company tomorrow and to proceed with consultation with
members to ask for a mandate” to strike, the labor union said
in an e-mailed statement today.  The union, which is asking for a 20 percent pay increase
for its members, is being offered 4.6 percent by the Anglo unit,
it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  